## Test Strategy

- Prefer unit tests for pure logic
- Use integration tests for boundaries
- Keep tests fast and deterministic
- Mock external dependencies consistently

## Test Patterns

### File Organization
- Test files alongside source or in `__tests__/`
- Match naming: `*.test.*`, `*.spec.*`
- Group by feature or module

### Coverage Expectations
- New features require tests
- Bug fixes include regression tests
- Maintain or improve coverage on changes

## For Code Generation

- Generate tests alongside new code
- Follow existing test patterns in the codebase
- Use the detected test framework
- Include happy path, edge cases, and error cases

## For Automations

- Verify tests pass before approving changes
- Flag untested code paths
- Generate test plan for large changes
- Check for flaky tests in CI results

## For Reviews

- Require tests for new functionality
- Check test quality, not just presence
- Verify mocking is appropriate and minimal
